#myCarousel.carousel.slide

  %ol.carousel-indicators
    %li.active{"data-slide-to" => "0", "data-target" => "#myCarousel"}
    %li{"data-slide-to" => "1", "data-target" => "#myCarousel"}
    %li{"data-slide-to" => "2", "data-target" => "#myCarousel"}
  .carousel-inner
    .item.active
      %img.img-responsive{src: "/assets/bg_suburb.jpg"}
        .container
          .carousel-caption
            %h1 Bootstrap 3 Carousel Layout
            %p
            %p
              %a.btn.btn-lg.btn-primary{href: "http://getbootstrap.com"} Learn More
    .item
      %img.img-responsive{src: "http://lorempixel.com/1500/600/abstract/1"}
        .container
          .carousel-caption
            %h1 Changes to the Grid
            %p Bootstrap 3 still features a 12-column grid, but many of the CSS class names have completely changed.
            %p
              %a.btn.btn-large.btn-primary{href: "#"} Learn more
    .item
      %img.img-responsive{src: "http://placehold.it/1500X500"}
        .container
          .carousel-caption
            %h1 Percentage-based sizing
            %p With "mobile-first" there is now only one percentage-based grid.
            %p
              %a.btn.btn-large.btn-primary{href: "#"} Browse gallery
      %a.left.carousel-control{"data-slide" => "prev", href: "#myCarousel"}
        %span.icon-prev
      %a.right.carousel-control{"data-slide" => "next", href: "#myCarousel"}
        %span.icon-next

.container.marketing
  / Three columns of text below the carousel
  .row
    .col-md-4.text-center
      %img.img-circle{src: "http://placehold.it/140x140"}
        %h2 Mobile-first
        %p Tablets, phones, laptops. The new 3 promises to be mobile friendly from the start.
        %p
          %a.btn.btn-default{href: "#"} View details »
    .col-md-4.text-center
      %img.img-circle{src: "http://placehold.it/140x140"}
        %h2 One Fluid Grid
        %p There is now just one percentage-based grid for Bootstrap 3. Customize for fixed widths.
        %p
          %a.btn.btn-default{href: "#"} View details »
    .col-md-4.text-center
      %img.img-circle{src: "http://placehold.it/140x140"}
        %h2 LESS is More
        %p Improved support for mixins make the new Bootstrap 3 easier to customize.
        %p
          %a.btn.btn-default{href: "#"} View details »

  %hr.featurette-divider
  .featurette
    %img.featurette-image.img-circle.pull-right{src: "http://placehold.it/512"}
      %h2.featurette-heading
        Responsive Design.
        %span.text-muted It'll blow your mind.
      %p.lead In simple terms, a responsive web design figures out what resolution of device it's being served on. Flexible grids then size correctly to fit the screen.
  %hr.featurette-divider
  .featurette
    %img.featurette-image.img-circle.pull-left{src: "http://placehold.it/512"}
      %h2.featurette-heading
        Smaller Footprint.
        %span.text-muted Lightweight.
      %p.lead The new Bootstrap 3 promises to be a smaller build. The separate Bootstrap base and responsive.css files have now been merged into one. There is no more fixed grid, only fluid.
  %hr.featurette-divider
  .featurette
    %img.featurette-image.img-circle.pull-right{src: "http://placehold.it/512"}
      %h2.featurette-heading
        And lastly, this one.
        %span.text-muted Flatness.
      %p.lead A big design trend for 2013 is "flat" design. Gone are the days of excessive gradients and shadows. Designers are producing cleaner flat designs, and Bootstrap 3 takes advantage of this minimalist trend.
  %hr.featurette-divider
  %footer
    %p.pull-right
      %a{href: "#"} Back to top
    %p
      This Bootstrap layout is compliments of Bootply. ·
      %a{href: "http://www.bootply.com/62603"} Edit on Bootply.com